Musician Ted Onulak is passionate about his music. His playing and singing
style are deeply rooted in the blues, and he lists such jazz greats as Charlie
Parker and John Lee Hooker as his musical influences. But his current career
only came about when fate intervened in his life. VOA's Tetiana Koprowicz
recently caught up with him and has more on how this former diplomat turned his
loss of eyesight into inspiration. Jim Bertel narrates.
